The paper deals with path planning, which is a common topic in robotics (cs.RO). The use of distance functions is also relevant to computer vision (cs.CV) and computational geometry (cs.CG). The paper also proposes a novel approach using f-divergence, which is a common concept in machine learning and artificial intelligence (cs.AI, cs.LG).
